HEADWORD: Repartimiento
<hw>Re`par*ti`mi*en"to</hw> <pr>(r?`p?r-t?`m?-?n"t?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., fr. <ets>repartir</ets> to divide.]</ety>
<def>A partition or distribution, especially of slaves; also, an
assessment of taxes.</def> <rj><au>W. Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

